@Report{RAII2022,
  author           = {{RAII}},
  date             = {2022},
  institution      = {Responsible Artificial Intelligence Institute},
  title            = {The Responsible {AI} Certification: Program Guidebook},
  eprint           = {https://assets.ctfassets.net/rz1q59puyoaw/5pyXogKSKNUKRkqOP4hRfy/5c5b525d0a77a1017643dcb6b5124634/RAII_Certification_Guidebook.pdf},
  comment          = {Say there was an international consensus on what constitutes responsible AI (RAI) Eitel-Poter et al., 2021

But that AI-related laws and regulations differ in scope, stringency and severity for non-compliance

RAII, a member of the World Economic Forum's (WEF) Global AI Action Alliance (GAIA), aims to address this inconsistency

RAII's main governance tool, the Responsible AI Certification Program is based on recurring themes, princples and gaps found by ``extensive review''. This assesses an organization's AI system against six dimensions: 
1. Systems Operations - s the functioning of the AI system
and key design choices related to the model and its data
  - System Scope and Function
  - Human-in-the-Loop
  - Model is Fit for Purpose
  - Data Relevance and Representativeness
  - Data Quality
2. Explainability and Interpretability
  - Communication about the Outcome (informing people of inputs and outputs)
  - Notification (to a person if a decision is made about them)
  - Recourse (to appeal a decision)
  -  Understanding the AI System's Decisions or Functions (extent of documents, reviews, publications of system information)
3. Accountability
  - Organizational Governance
  - Team Governance
4 Consumer Protection
  - Transparency to the User and Data Subject
  - Harm to Individuals (potential to harm users)
  - Protections (individual or group's privacy)
5. Bias and Fairness
  - Bias Impacts (mitigation of bias)
  - Bias Training (education of designers, developers, users and those impacted)
  - Bias Testing (of models, algorithms and datasets)
6. Robustness
  - Data Drift (processes and procedures for combatting)
  - System Acceptance Test Performed (extent of exposure to edge cases)
  - Contingency Planning (extent of preparedness for  adversarial attacks, load inputs, and other edge cases and extreme
scenarios)

Developed assessment and scoring method for assessment and certification. To earn certification, the AI system must earn 50\5+ of available score for each of the 6 dimensions - the total is then used to give an overall assessment (needs improvement, satisfactory, good, excellent) and a level (certified, silver, gold, platinum).},
  creationdate     = {2024-01-08T10:37:21},
  keywords         = {trust, AI, responsible, ethics, bureaucracy, ResponsibleAI},
  modificationdate = {2024-01-30T10:00:34},
  owner            = {ISargent},
}

