- inclusive
- discursive
- deliberative
- pluralistic
- reflexive
- participatory

Technical ``progress'' is no longer linear, instead: p263
-  complex,  dynamic  pictures  of  contingency
- social shaping
- coconstruction
- path dependency
- momentum
- lock-in
- autonomy
- entrapment

``In short, innovation is a vector, rather than just a scalar quantity''  p263

Highlights the normative ideas of technological progress as good p264

``The starting point for this analysis is a distinction between parallel, interlinked, and mutually coconstituting processes of commitment and appraisal in technology governance ... '' p265 

``Appraisal is ... a necessary precondition for intentional commitments, yet only circumstantially so informed in return. This asymmetry between appraisal and commitment raises  questions  for current participatory discourses. In short, what is the purpose of structured exercises in participation? Are they  about informing, or actually forming, the commitments themselves?'' p267

