  abstract         = {Public support for climate policy is required for policy adoption, stringency and stability. This chapter explains why citizens hold different climate policy attitudes. Six types of factors are discussed. 
1. Personal factors, such as socio-demographics, climate change perceptions, values and ideologies
2. Social perceptions and identities, that is, people value climate policy differently depending on what other people think
