  issn             = {0305-9006},
  pages            = {1-32},
  url              = {https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0305900615000306},
  volume           = {109},
  comment          = {Huge paper considering transport planning for reducing traffic and GHG emissions. Use structural and causal analyses, literature studies and case studies (using planning documents and semi-structured interviews)

Interesting for methodology of identify [best practice] solutions and seeing if decision-makers use these and, if not, why not. From this understand what mechanisms limit the way decision-makers use expertise

Identified theoretical explanations for actions of planners and then searched for evidence statements for these (in documents and interviews) and used these to critically discuss if the explanation was relevant in the concrete case

